[src:robust-regression/m-estimator] A proof of this property of M-estimators can be found in Huber (1981, Section 3.2).
[src:robust-regression/m-estimator] M-estimators can be constructed for location parameters and scale parameters in univariate and multivariate settings, as well as being used in robust regression.
[src:robust-regression/m-estimator] Let (*X*1, ..., *X**n*) be a set of independent, identically distributed random variables, with distribution *F*.
